Q: Sample qmake command?
/usr/bin/qmake-qt4 -spec /usr/lib64/qt4/mkspecs/linux-g++-64 -o Makefile ../01_hello_world_button/01_hello_world_button.pro
or simply
qmake-qt4 ../01_hello_world_button/01_hello_world_button.pro

qmake-qt4 -project                              # build project file based on extensions

Q: Qmake directive in pro file ?
TEMPLATE = app                                  # This is an application type project (not a library or plugin or ...)
TARGET = hello_world
QT = core gui
QT += network opengl sql xml support            # Add QtNetwork, QtopenGL, .... libraries to the build 
QT -= network                                   # Remove QtNetwork library requirement

TRANSLATIONS =  application_fr.ts \             # Translation files to be used by QtLinguist (see lupdate, lrelease commands)
                application_nl.ts

RESOURCES = symbols.qrc                         # Resource file that needs to be compiled (file points to files to be included in resource)

CONFIG =
FORMS  =                                        # ui files 


Q: The generated makefile?
make clean                                      # Remove all the intermediary files
make distclean                                  # Remove intermediary files + built files



